<ansi fg="black-bold">.:</ansi> <ansi fg="red-bold">Admin Help for </ansi><ansi fg="command">election</ansi>

  <ansi fg="yellow">Managing Elections</ansi>

    <ansi fg="command">election start <title></ansi>
      Starts a new election for the zone you are currently in.
      <title> becomes the elected title (e.g. "Mayor of Frostfang").
      Only one election may be active at a time.

    <ansi fg="command">election end</ansi>
      Immediately ends the active election and tallies votes.
      The candidate with the most votes wins. Ties are broken
      randomly. If no votes were cast, no winner is recorded.

  <ansi fg="yellow">Tax Rate Override</ansi>

    <ansi fg="command">election taxrate <0-100></ansi>
      Sets the tax rate for the zone you are currently in.

    <ansi fg="command">election taxrate <zone> <0-100></ansi>
      Sets the tax rate for any named zone regardless of your
      current location.

    Tax is charged on top of listed shop prices in the zone.
    The extra gold flows into the zone coffer. Default is 1%.
    A rate of 0 disables the tax entirely.

    Note: elected officials set the tax rate in-game via
    <ansi fg="command">taxrate <0-100></ansi> while standing in their zone's coffer room.

  <ansi fg="yellow">Room Tags</ansi>

    <ansi fg="cyan">election poll</ansi>      - Polling location. Players nominate and vote here.
    <ansi fg="cyan">coffer</ansi>             - Zone coffer room. Title-holder manages gold here.
                         Elected official sets tax rate here.
    <ansi fg="cyan">elected officials only</ansi> - Restricted area. Only the title-holder and
                         their active party may enter.

  <ansi fg="yellow">Config Keys</ansi>  (Modules.elections.* in config overrides)

    <ansi fg="white-bold">ElectionDuration</ansi>     - How long an election runs (default: "2 days").
    <ansi fg="white-bold">ElectionCyclePeriod</ansi>  - Time between automatic re-elections
                         (default: "1 year"). Empty string disables.
    <ansi fg="white-bold">TitleColor</ansi>           - Color code or pattern for winner titles
                         shown after player names (default: "158").

